HEA_composition.average_particle_size_nm: Porous nanosheet arrays with thickness ≈10 nm

synthesis.precursors: Co, Fe, Ni, Mo, W metal salts and Te powder

reaction_conditions.post_synthesis: Dried at 60 °C after deposition, tellurization at 300 °C

XRD.crystal_structure: Amorphous structure observed, no distinct crystalline peaks except for carbon paper peaks

XPS.EDS: Elemental distribution uniform, Te incorporated homogeneously

electrochemical_performance.mass_activity: CoFeNiMoWTe shows higher mass activity than CoFeNiMoW and Co3O4 (Figure 2g)
electrochemical_performance.stability: Stability maintained for 100 hours at 10 mA/cm² with only a 28 mV increase in overpotential

theoretical_computations.reaction_mechanism: Enhanced OER performance attributed to the synergy of high mixed entropy and increased corrosion-resistance from Mo and W, with Te enhancing glass forming ability and catalytic active sites.
